article_text:
Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, newly re-elected as head of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party, outlined his new economic agenda Wednesday. The stock market seemed impressed, with a 7.7% rally, although the Tokyo exchange is becoming as volatile as Shanghai’s these days. So is Abenomics about to gain traction at last?

Not likely. For all his energy and eagerness, the Prime Minister still shrinks from the necessary economic reform....

twitter.description: Japan’s Prime Minister Shinzo Abe still hasn’t shot his third reform arrow, says an editorial in The Wall Street Journal.
twitter.title: Rebooting Abenomics

Prime Minister Shinzo Abe, newly re-elected as head of the ruling Liberal Democratic Party, outlined his new economic agenda Wednesday.
For all his energy and eagerness, the Prime Minister still shrinks from the necessary economic reform....
So is Abenomics about to gain traction at last?
The stock market seemed impressed, with a 7.7% rally, although the Tokyo exchange is becoming as volatile as Shanghai’s these days.
Not likely.
